messages.message:
Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': '--- a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c\n+++ b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c\n@@ -3257,8 +3257,14 @@\n     if (initialised) {\n-        wrefresh(stdscr);\n-        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);\n+        if (stdscr == NULL) {\n+            PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);\n+            return NULL;\n+        }\n+        wrefresh(stdscr);\n+        return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);\n     }\n \n     win = initscr();\n'}`
responded: The root cause of the null dereference is in this code in `_curses_initscr_impl`:

```c
if (initialised) {
    wrefresh(stdscr);
    return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
}
```

If `initialised` is true but `stdscr` is NULL, then both `wrefresh(stdscr)` and `PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL)` will dereference a null pointer, causing a crash.

**Fix:**  
Add a check to ensure `stdscr` is not NULL before using it when `initialised` is true. If it is NULL, set an error and return NULL.

Here is the patch:

args.patch:
diff --git a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
index d32cff66144..09e183f9b37 100644
--- a/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
+++ b/Modules/_cursesmodule.c
@@ -3255,6 +3255,10 @@ _curses_initscr_impl(PyObject *module)
     PyCursesWindowObject *winobj;

     if (initialised) {
+        if (stdscr == NULL) {
+            PyErr_SetString(PyCursesError, catchall_NULL);
+            return NULL;
+        }
         wrefresh(stdscr);
         return (PyObject *)PyCursesWindow_New(stdscr, NULL);
     }

